Removed direct imports of babel-types and babel-template

[Add] Support for object rest properties

Currently invalid syntax is output when transforming object rest
properties. The rewiring seems to work as expected if we simply skip
rewiring rest properties.

See: https://github.com/tc39/proposal-object-rest-spread

[Test] Add test case for object rest properties

Check that "object rest properties" work (basically "LValue spreads" for
objects).
An example of an object rest property would be `metadata` in the
following piece of code:

    const { id, name, ...metadata } = newUser

This commit adds a test case to check that this syntax is supported.
(It's currently not)

Reference: https://github.com/tc39/proposal-object-rest-spread

Add test cases for missing JSX support

It turned out that babel-plugin-rewire doesn’t allow to override
both `React` and `Component` in `React.createClass(Component)`
generated from JSX code `<Component />`.

After debugging I realized that `React` and `Component`
aren’t wrapped into `__get__` calls.

The commit adds test cases for the described problem.

Update fixtures with added ability to assign undefined

Add an ability to redefine a dependency to undefined

Previously getter was checking if the value is undefined, and if it's
undefined then it was returning the original value.

The commit adds an ability to assign undefined by introducing
a "intentional undefined" constant used in the getter and the setter.

Add a test case for an ability to redefined a dependency to undefined

Right now the plugin doesn't allow to set undefined as the value in
the getter.

It's useful when you need to emulate a missing features, e.g:

```js
const localStorage = window.localStorage
// In a test:
__Rewire__('localStorage', undefined)
```

Don't apply runtime transforms for usage tests

Runtime transformations in usage tests add ES6 import code when using
Object.defineProperty or similar methods. They are added after es2015
preset has already been ran, so the compiled code will still have
incompatible "import" calls, crashing the tests eventually.

add Noi

Modifying *all* <code> blocks to remove whitespace after <code>
to fix improper markdown formatting.

Swapping all spaces with global &nbsp (non-blocking spaces) causes
issues with word-wrap. To solve this we now only have nbsp when we
encounter spaces or a tab at the start of a line (to maintain indentation).

A fiddle exists to test the regex at:
https://jsfiddle.net/xtraeme/x34ao9jp/13/

Improved exportMarkdown() & getName() to better preserve user input:
* Maintains proper carriage returns in markdown output
* Indented spaces / tabs are converted to   then run through ExportMD

Also added stub code to improve readability of exported filenames, but this will likely also require changes to some of the Rust code

Fix GPU not being used even when it available

On lots of systems onnxruntime doesn't detect GPU unless pytorch is imported before it. So despite having CUDA and CUDNN setup correctly, it is only using CPUExecutionProvider. By importing pytorch first, the issue is fixed. So let's use this until any official solution is available.

to fix improper markdown formatting.

* Indented spaces / tabs are converted to   then run through ExportMD

Fix GPU not being used even when it available

On lots of systems onnxruntime doesn't detect GPU unless pytorch is imported before it. So despite having CUDA and CUDNN setup correctly, it is only using CPUExecutionProvider. By importing pytorch first, the issue is fixed. So let's use this until any official solution is available.
